2Sm22:44 You rescued me from my stubborn people and made me the leader of foreign nations, who are now my slaves.
2Sm22:45 They obey and come crawling.
2Sm22:46 They have lost all courage and from their fortresses they come trembling.
2Sm22:47 You are the living Lord ! I will praise you! You are a mighty rock. I will honor you for keeping me safe.
2Sm22:48 You took revenge for me, and you put nations in my power.
2Sm22:49 You protected me from violent enemies, and you made me much greater than all of them.
2Sm22:50 I will praise you, Lord , and I will honor you among the nations.
2Sm22:51 You give glorious victories to your chosen king. Your faithful love for David and for his descendants will never end.
