Psa13:1 How much longer, Lord , will you forget about me? Will it be forever? How long will you hide?
Psa13:2 How long must I be confused and miserable all day? How long will my enemies keep beating me down?
Psa13:3 Please listen, Lord God, and answer my prayers. Make my eyes sparkle again, or else I will fall into the sleep of death.
Psa13:4 My enemies will say, "Now we've won!" They will be greatly pleased when I am defeated.
Psa13:5 I trust your love, and I feel like celebrating because you rescued me.
Psa13:6 You have been good to me, Lord , and I will sing about you.
Psa14:1 Only a fool would say, "There is no God!" People like that are worthless; they are heartless and cruel and never do right.
