Psa24:5 The Lord God, who saves them, will bless and reward them,
Psa24:6 because they worship and serve the God of Jacob.
Psa24:7 Open the ancient gates, so that the glorious king may come in.
Psa24:8 Who is this glorious king? He is our Lord , a strong and mighty warrior.
Psa24:9 Open the ancient gates, so that the glorious king may come in.
Psa24:10 Who is this glorious king? He is our Lord , the All-Powerful!
Psa25:1 I offer you my heart, Lord God,
Psa25:2 and I trust you. Don't make me ashamed or let enemies defeat me.
Psa25:3 Don't disappoint any of your worshipers, but disappoint all deceitful liars.
Psa25:4 Show me your paths and teach me to follow;
Psa25:5 guide me by your truth and instruct me. You keep me safe, and I always trust you.
Psa25:6 Please, Lord , remember, you have always been patient and kind.
Psa25:7 Forget each wrong I did when I was young. Show how truly kind you are and remember me.
Psa25:8 You are honest and merciful, and you teach sinners how to follow your path.
Psa25:9 You lead humble people to do what is right and to stay on your path.
Psa25:10 In everything you do, you are kind and faithful to everyone who keeps our agreement with you.
Psa25:11 Be true to your name, Lord , by forgiving each one of my terrible sins.
Psa25:12 You will show the right path to all who worship you.
Psa25:13 They will have plenty, and then their children will receive the land.
Psa25:14 Our Lord , you are the friend of your worshipers, and you make an agreement with all of us.
Psa25:15 I always look to you, because you rescue me from every trap.
Psa25:16 I am lonely and troubled. Show that you care and have pity on me.
Psa25:17 My awful worries keep growing. Rescue me from sadness.
Psa25:18 See my troubles and misery and forgive my sins.
Psa25:19 Look at all my enemies! See how much they hate me.
Psa25:20 I come to you for shelter. Protect me, keep me safe, and don't disappoint me.
Psa25:21 I obey you with all my heart, and I trust you, knowing that you will save me.
Psa25:22 Our God, please save Israel from all of its troubles.
Psa26:1 Show that I am right, Lord ! I stay true to myself, and I have trusted you without doubting.
Psa26:2 Test my thoughts and find out what I am like.
Psa26:3 I never forget your kindness, and I am always faithful to you.
Psa26:4 I don't spend my time with worthless liars
Psa26:5 or go with evil crowds.
Psa26:6 I wash my hands, Lord , to show my innocence, and I worship at your altar,
Psa26:7 while gratefully singing about your wonders.
Psa26:8 I love the temple where you live, and where your glory shines.
Psa26:9 Don't sweep me away, as you do sinners. Don't punish me with death as you do those people who are brutal
Psa26:10 or full of meanness or who bribe others.
Psa26:11 I stay true to myself. Be kind and rescue me.
Psa26:12 Now I stand on solid ground! And when your people meet, I will praise you, Lord .
Psa27:1 You, Lord , are the light that keeps me safe. I am not afraid of anyone. You protect me, and I have no fears.
Psa27:2 Brutal people may attack and try to kill me, but they will stumble. Fierce enemies may attack, but they will fall.
Psa27:3 Armies may surround me, but I won't be afraid; war may break out, but I will trust you.
