Psa28:8 You give strength to your people, Lord , and you save and protect your chosen ones.
Psa28:9 Come save us and bless us. Be our shepherd and always carry us in your arms.
Psa29:1 All of you angels in heaven, honor the glory and power of the Lord !
Psa29:2 Honor the wonderful name of the Lord , and worship the Lord most holy and glorious.
Psa29:3 The voice of the Lord echoes over the oceans. The glorious Lord God thunders above the roar of the raging sea,
Psa29:4 and his voice is mighty and marvelous.
Psa29:5 The voice of the Lord destroys the cedar trees; the Lord shatters cedars on Mount Lebanon.
Psa29:6 God makes Mount Lebanon skip like a calf and Mount Hermon jump like a wild ox.
Psa29:7 The voice of the Lord makes lightning flash
Psa29:8 and the desert tremble. And because of the Lord , the desert near Kadesh shivers and shakes.
Psa29:9 The voice of the Lord makes deer give birth before their time. Forests are stripped of leaves, and the temple is filled with shouts of praise.
Psa29:10 The Lord rules on his throne, king of the flood forever.
Psa29:11 Pray that our Lord will make us strong and give us peace.
Psa30:1 I will praise you, Lord ! You saved me from the grave and kept my enemies from celebrating my death.
Psa30:2 I prayed to you, Lord God, and you healed me,
Psa30:3 saving me from death and the grave.
Psa30:4 Your faithful people, Lord , will praise you with songs and honor your holy name.
Psa30:5 Your anger lasts a little while, but your kindness lasts for a lifetime. At night we may cry, but when morning comes we will celebrate.
Psa30:6 I was carefree and thought, "I'll never be shaken!"
Psa30:7 You, Lord , were my friend, and you made me strong as a mighty mountain. But when you hid your face, I was crushed.
Psa30:8 I prayed to you, Lord , and in my prayer I said,
Psa30:9 "What good will it do you if I am in the grave? Once I have turned to dust, how can I praise you or tell how loyal you are?
Psa30:10 Have pity, Lord ! Help!"
Psa30:11 You have turned my sorrow into joyful dancing. No longer am I sad and wearing sackcloth.
Psa30:12 I thank you from my heart, and I will never stop singing your praises, my Lord and my God.
Psa31:1 I come to you, Lord , for protection. Don't let me be ashamed. Do as you have promised and rescue me.
Psa31:2 Listen to my prayer and hurry to save me. Be my mighty rock and the fortress where I am safe.
Psa31:3 You, Lord God, are my mighty rock and my fortress. Lead me and guide me, so that your name will be honored.
Psa31:4 Protect me from hidden traps and keep me safe.
Psa31:5 You are faithful, and I trust you because you rescued me.
Psa31:6 I hate the worshipers of worthless idols, but I trust you, Lord .
Psa31:7 I celebrate and shout because you are kind. You saw all my suffering, and you cared for me.
Psa31:8 You kept me from the hands of my enemies, and you set me free.
Psa31:9 Have pity, Lord ! I am hurting and almost blind. My whole body aches.
Psa31:10 I have known only sorrow all my life long, and I suffer year after year. I am weak from sin, and my bones are limp.
Psa31:11 My enemies insult me. Neighbors are even worse, and I disgust my friends. People meet me on the street, and they turn and run.
Psa31:12 I am completely forgotten like someone dead. I am merely a broken dish.
Psa31:13 I hear the crowds whisper, "Everyone is afraid!" They are plotting and scheming to murder me.
Psa31:14 But I trust you, Lord , and I claim you as my God.
Psa31:15 My life is in your hands. Save me from enemies who hunt me down.
Psa31:16 Smile on me, your servant. Have pity and rescue me.
Psa31:17 I pray only to you. Don't disappoint me. Disappoint my cruel enemies until they lie silent in their graves.
Psa31:18 Silence those proud liars! Make them stop bragging and insulting your people.
Psa31:19 You are wonderful, and while everyone watches, you store up blessings for all who honor and trust you.
Psa31:20 You are their shelter from harmful plots, and you are their protection from vicious gossip.
Psa31:21 I will praise you, Lord , for showing great kindness when I was like a city under attack.
Psa31:22 I was terrified and thought, "They've chased me far away from you!" But you answered my prayer when I shouted for help.
Psa31:23 All who belong to the Lord , show how you love him. The Lord protects the faithful, but he severely punishes everyone who is proud.
Psa31:24 All who trust the Lord , be cheerful and strong.
Psa32:1 Our God, you bless everyone whose sins you forgive and wipe away.
Psa32:2 You bless them by saying, "You told me your sins, without trying to hide them, and now I forgive you."
