Psa32:4 Night and day your hand weighed heavily on me, and my strength was gone as in the summer heat.
Psa32:5 So I confessed my sins and told them all to you. I said, "I'll tell the Lord each one of my sins." Then you forgave me and took away my guilt.
Psa32:6 We worship you, Lord, and we should always pray whenever we find out that we have sinned. Then we won't be swept away by a raging flood.
Psa32:7 You are my hiding place! You protect me from trouble, and you put songs in my heart because you have saved me.
Psa32:8 You said to me, "I will point out the road that you should follow. I will be your teacher and watch over you.
Psa32:9 Don't be stupid like horses and mules that must be led with ropes to make them obey."
Psa32:10 All kinds of troubles will strike the wicked, but your kindness shields those who trust you, Lord .
