Psa97:8 When the people of Zion and of the towns of Judah hear that God brings justice, they will celebrate.
Psa97:9 The Lord rules the whole earth, and he is more glorious than all the false gods.
Psa97:10 Love the Lord and hate evil! God protects his loyal people and rescues them from violence.
Psa97:11 If you obey and do right, a light will show you the way and fill you with happiness.
Psa97:12 You are the Lord 's people! So celebrate and praise the only God.
Psa98:1 Sing a new song to the Lord ! He has worked miracles, and with his own powerful arm, he has won the victory.
Psa98:2 The Lord has shown the nations that he has the power to save and to bring justice.
Psa98:3 God has been faithful in his love for Israel, and his saving power is seen everywhere on earth.
Psa98:4 Tell everyone on this earth to sing happy songs in praise of the Lord .
Psa98:5 Make music for him on harps. Play beautiful melodies!
Psa98:6 Sound the trumpets and horns and celebrate with joyful songs for our Lord and King!
Psa98:7 Command the ocean to roar with all of its creatures, and the earth to shout with all of its people.
Psa98:8 Order the rivers to clap their hands, and all of the hills to sing together.
Psa98:9 Let them worship the Lord ! He is coming to judge everyone on the earth, and he will be honest and fair.
Psa99:1 Our Lord , you are King! You rule from your throne above the winged creatures, as people tremble and the earth shakes.
Psa99:2 You are praised in Zion, and you control all nations.
Psa99:3 Only you are God! And your power alone, so great and fearsome, is worthy of praise.
Psa99:4 You are our mighty King, a lover of fairness, who sees that justice is done everywhere in Israel.
Psa99:5 Our Lord and our God, we praise you and kneel down to worship you, the God of holiness!
Psa99:6 Moses and Aaron were two of your priests. Samuel was also one of those who prayed in your name, and you, our Lord , answered their prayers.
Psa99:7 You spoke to them from a thick cloud, and they obeyed your laws.
Psa99:8 Our Lord and our God, you answered their prayers and forgave their sins, but when they did wrong, you punished them.
Psa99:9 We praise you, Lord God, and we worship you at your sacred mountain. Only you are God!
Psa100:1 Shout praises to the Lord , everyone on this earth.
Psa100:2 Be joyful and sing as you come in to worship the Lord !
Psa100:3 You know the Lord is God! He created us, and we belong to him; we are his people, the sheep in his pasture.
Psa100:4 Be thankful and praise the Lord as you enter his temple.
Psa100:5 The Lord is good! His love and faithfulness will last forever.
Psa101:1 I will sing to you, Lord ! I will celebrate your kindness and your justice.
Psa101:2 Please help me learn to do the right thing, and I will be honest and fair in my own kingdom.
Psa101:3 I refuse to be corrupt or to take part in anything crooked,
Psa101:4 and I won't be dishonest or deceitful.
Psa101:5 Anyone who spreads gossip will be silenced, and no one who is conceited will be my friend.
Psa101:6 I will find trustworthy people to serve as my advisors, and only an honest person will serve as an official.
Psa101:7 No one who cheats or lies will have a position in my royal court.
Psa101:8 Each morning I will silence any lawbreakers I find in the countryside or in the city of the Lord .
Psa102:1 I pray to you, Lord ! Please listen.
Psa102:2 Don't hide from me in my time of trouble. Pay attention to my prayer and quickly give an answer.
Psa102:3 My days disappear like smoke, and my bones are burning as though in a furnace.
Psa102:4 I am wasting away like grass, and my appetite is gone.
Psa102:5 My groaning never stops, and my bones can be seen through my skin.
Psa102:6 I am like a lonely owl in the desert
Psa102:7 or a restless sparrow alone on a roof.
Psa102:8 My enemies insult me all day, and they use my name for a curse word.
Psa102:9 Instead of food, I have ashes to eat and tears to drink,
Psa102:10 because you are furious and have thrown me aside.
Psa102:11 My life fades like a shadow at the end of day and withers like grass.
Psa102:12 Our Lord , you are King forever and will always be famous.
Psa102:13 You will show pity to Zion because the time has come.
Psa102:14 We, your servants, love each stone in the city, and we are sad to see them lying in the dirt.
Psa102:15 Our Lord , the nations will honor you, and all kings on earth will praise your glory.
Psa102:16 You will rebuild the city of Zion. Your glory will be seen,
Psa102:17 and the prayers of the homeless will be answered.
Psa102:18 Future generations must also praise the Lord , so write this for them:
Psa102:19 "From his holy temple, the Lord looked down at the earth.
Psa102:20 He listened to the groans of prisoners, and he rescued everyone who was doomed to die."
Psa102:21 All Jerusalem should praise you, our Lord ,
Psa102:22 when people from every nation meet to worship you.
Psa102:23 I should still be strong, but you, Lord , have made an old person of me.
Psa102:24 You will live forever! Years mean nothing to you. Don't cut my life in half!
Psa102:25 In the beginning, Lord , you laid the earth's foundation and created the heavens.
Psa102:26 They will all disappear and wear out like clothes. You change them, as you would a coat, but you last forever.
Psa102:27 You are always the same. Years cannot change you.
Psa102:28 Every generation of those who serve you will live in your presence.
Psa103:1 With all my heart I praise the Lord , and with all that I am I praise his holy name!
Psa103:2 With all my heart I praise the Lord ! I will never forget how kind he has been.
Psa103:3 The Lord forgives our sins, heals us when we are sick,
Psa103:4 and protects us from death. His kindness and love are a crown on our heads.
Psa103:5 Each day that we live, he provides for our needs and gives us the strength of a young eagle.
Psa103:6 For all who are mistreated, the Lord brings justice.
Psa103:7 He taught his Law to Moses and showed all Israel what he could do.
Psa103:8 The Lord is merciful! He is kind and patient, and his love never fails.
Psa103:9 The Lord won't always be angry and point out our sins;
Psa103:10 he doesn't punish us as our sins deserve.
Psa103:11 How great is God's love for all who worship him? Greater than the distance between heaven and earth!
Psa103:12 How far has the Lord taken our sins from us? Farther than the distance from east to west!
Psa103:13 Just as parents are kind to their children, the Lord is kind to all who worship him,
Psa103:14 because he knows we are made of dust.
Psa103:15 We humans are like grass or wild flowers that quickly bloom.
Psa103:16 But a scorching wind blows, and they quickly wither to be forever forgotten.
Psa103:17 The Lord is always kind to those who worship him, and he keeps his promises to their descendants
Psa103:18 who faithfully obey him.
Psa103:19 God has set up his kingdom in heaven, and he rules the whole creation.
Psa103:20 All of you mighty angels, who obey God's commands, come and praise your Lord !
Psa103:21 All of you thousands who serve and obey God, come and praise your Lord !
Psa103:22 All of God's creation and all that he rules, come and praise your Lord ! With all my heart I praise the Lord !
Psa104:1 I praise you, Lord God, with all my heart. You are glorious and majestic, dressed in royal robes
Psa104:2 and surrounded by light. You spread out the sky like a tent,
Psa104:3 and you built your home over the mighty ocean. The clouds are your chariot with the wind as its wings.
Psa104:4 The winds are your messengers, and flames of fire are your servants.
Psa104:5 You built foundations for the earth, and it will never be shaken.
Psa104:6 You covered the earth with the ocean that rose above the mountains.
Psa104:7 Then your voice thundered! And the water flowed
Psa104:8 down the mountains and through the valleys to the place you prepared.
Psa104:9 Now you have set boundaries, so that the water will never flood the earth again.
Psa104:10 You provide streams of water in the hills and valleys,
Psa104:11 so that the donkeys and other wild animals can satisfy their thirst.
Psa104:12 Birds build their nests nearby and sing in the trees.
Psa104:13 From your home above you send rain on the hills and water the earth.
Psa104:14 You let the earth produce grass for cattle, plants for our food,
Psa104:15 wine to cheer us up, olive oil for our skin, and grain for our health.
Psa104:16 Our Lord , your trees always have water, and so do the cedars you planted in Lebanon.
Psa104:17 Birds nest in those trees, and storks make their home in the fir trees.
Psa104:18 Wild goats find a home in the tall mountains, and small animals can hide between the rocks.
Psa104:19 You created the moon to tell us the seasons. The sun knows when to set,
Psa104:20 and you made the darkness, so the animals in the forest could come out at night.
Psa104:21 Lions roar as they hunt for the food you provide.
Psa104:22 But when morning comes, they return to their dens,
Psa104:23 then we go out to work until the end of day.
Psa104:24 Our Lord , by your wisdom you made so many things; the whole earth is covered with your living creatures.
Psa104:25 But what about the ocean so big and wide? It is alive with creatures, large and small.
Psa104:26 And there are the ships, as well as Leviathan, the monster you created to splash in the sea.
Psa104:27 All of these depend on you to provide them with food,
Psa104:28 and you feed each one with your own hand, until they are full.
Psa104:29 But when you turn away, they are terrified; when you end their life, they die and rot.
Psa104:30 You created all of them by your Spirit, and you give new life to the earth.
Psa104:31 Our Lord , we pray that your glory will last forever and that you will be pleased with what you have done.
Psa104:32 You look at the earth, and it trembles. You touch the mountains, and smoke goes up.
Psa104:33 As long as I live, I will sing and praise you, the Lord God.
Psa104:34 I hope my thoughts will please you, because you are the one who makes me glad.
Psa104:35 Destroy all wicked sinners from the earth once and for all. With all my heart I praise you, Lord ! I praise you!
Psa105:1 Praise the Lord and pray in his name! Tell everyone what he has done.
Psa105:2 Sing praises to the Lord ! Tell about his miracles.
Psa105:3 Celebrate and worship his holy name with all your heart.
Psa105:4 Trust the Lord and his mighty power.
Psa105:5 Remember his miracles and all his wonders and his fair decisions.
Psa105:6 You belong to the family of Abraham, his servant; you are his chosen ones, the descendants of Jacob.
Psa105:7 The Lord is our God, bringing justice everywhere on earth.
Psa105:8 He will never forget his agreement or his promises, not in thousands of years.
Psa105:9 God made an eternal promise
Psa105:10 to Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob,
Psa105:11 when he said, "I'll give you the land of Canaan."
Psa105:12 At the time there were only a few of us, and we were homeless.
Psa105:13 We wandered from nation to nation, from one country to another.
Psa105:14 God did not let anyone mistreat our people. Instead he protected us by punishing rulers
Psa105:15 and telling them, "Don't touch my chosen leaders or harm my prophets!"
Psa105:16 God kept crops from growing until food was scarce everywhere in the land.
Psa105:17 But he had already sent Joseph, sold as a slave into Egypt,
Psa105:18 with chains of iron around his legs and neck.
Psa105:19 Joseph remained a slave until his own words had come true, and the Lord had finished testing him.
Psa105:20 Then the king of Egypt set Joseph free
Psa105:21 and put him in charge of everything he owned.
Psa105:22 Joseph was in command of the officials, and he taught the leaders how to use wisdom.
Psa105:23 Jacob and his family came and settled in Egypt as foreigners.
Psa105:24 They were the Lord 's people, so he let them grow stronger than their enemies.
Psa105:25 They served the Lord , and he made the Egyptians plan hateful things against them.
Psa105:26 God sent his servant Moses. He also chose and sent Aaron
Psa105:27 to his people in Egypt, and they worked miracles and wonders there.
Psa105:28 Moses and Aaron obeyed God, and he sent darkness to cover Egypt.
Psa105:29 God turned their rivers into streams of blood, and the fish all died.
Psa105:30 Frogs were everywhere, even in the royal palace.
Psa105:31 When God gave the command, flies and gnats swarmed all around.
Psa105:32 In place of rain, God sent hailstones and flashes of lightning.
Psa105:33 He destroyed their grapevines and their fig trees, and he made splinters of all the other trees.
Psa105:34 God gave the command, and more grasshoppers came than could be counted.
Psa105:35 They ate every green plant and all the crops that grew in the land of Egypt.
Psa105:36 Then God took the life of every first-born son.
Psa105:37 When God led Israel from Egypt, they took silver and gold, and no one was left behind.
Psa105:38 The Egyptians were afraid and gladly let them go.
Psa105:39 God hid them under a cloud and guided them by fire during the night.
Psa105:40 When they asked for food, he sent more birds than they could eat.
Psa105:41 God even split open a rock, and streams of water gushed into the desert.
Psa105:42 God never forgot his sacred promise to his servant Abraham.
Psa105:43 When the Lord rescued his chosen people from Egypt, they celebrated with songs.
Psa105:44 The Lord gave them the land and everything else the nations had worked for.
Psa105:45 He did this so that his people would obey all of his laws. Shout praises to the Lord !
Psa106:1 We will celebrate and praise you, Lord ! You are good to us, and your love never fails.
Psa106:2 No one can praise you enough for all of the mighty things you have done.
Psa106:3 You bless those people who are honest and fair in everything they do.
Psa106:4 Remember me, Lord , when you show kindness by saving your people.
Psa106:5 Let me prosper with the rest of your chosen ones, as they celebrate with pride because they belong to you.
Psa106:6 We and our ancestors have sinned terribly.
Psa106:7 When they were in Egypt, they paid no attention to your marvelous deeds or your wonderful love. And they turned against you at the Red Sea.
Psa106:8 But you were true to your name, and you rescued them to prove how mighty you are.
Psa106:9 You said to the Red Sea,  "Dry up!" Then you led your people across on land as dry as a desert.
Psa106:10 You saved all of them
Psa106:11 and drowned every one of their enemies.
Psa106:12 Then your people trusted you and sang your praises.
Psa106:13 But they soon forgot what you had done and rejected your advice.
Psa106:14 They became greedy for food and tested you there in the desert.
Psa106:15 So you gave them what they wanted, but later you destroyed them with a horrible disease.
Psa106:16 Everyone in camp was jealous of Moses and of Aaron, your chosen priest.
Psa106:17 Dathan and Abiram rebelled, and the earth opened up and swallowed them.
Psa106:18 Then fire broke out and destroyed all of their followers.
Psa106:19 At Horeb your people made and worshiped the statue
Psa106:20 of a bull, instead of you, their glorious God.
Psa106:21 You worked powerful miracles to save them from Egypt, but they forgot about you
Psa106:22 and the fearsome things you did at the Red Sea.
Psa106:23 You were angry and started to destroy them, but Moses, your chosen leader, begged you not to do it.
Psa106:24 They would not trust you, Lord , and they did not like the promised land.
Psa106:25 They would not obey you, and they grumbled in their tents.
Psa106:26 So you threatened them by saying, "I'll kill you out here in the desert!
Psa106:27 I'll scatter your children everywhere in the world."
Psa106:28 Your people became followers of a god named Baal Peor, and they ate sacrifices offered to the dead.
Psa106:29 They did such terrible things that you punished them with a deadly disease.
Psa106:30 But Phinehas helped them, and the sickness stopped.
Psa106:31 Now he will always be highly honored.
Psa106:32 At Meribah Spring they turned against you and made you furious.
Psa106:33 Then Moses got into trouble for speaking in anger.
Psa106:34 Our Lord , they disobeyed you by refusing to destroy the nations.
Psa106:35 Instead they were friendly with those foreigners and followed their customs.
Psa106:36 Then they fell into the trap of worshiping idols.
Psa106:37 They sacrificed their sons and their daughters to demons
Psa106:38 and to the gods of Canaan. Then they poured out the blood of these innocent children and made the land filthy.
Psa106:39 By doing such gruesome things, they also became filthy.
Psa106:40 Finally, Lord , you were angry and terribly disgusted with your people.
Psa106:41 So you put them in the power of nations that hated them.
Psa106:42 They were mistreated and abused by their enemies,
Psa106:43 but you saved them time after time. They were determined to rebel, and their sins caused their downfall.
Psa106:44 You answered their prayers when they were in trouble.
Psa106:45 You kept your agreement and were so merciful
Psa106:46 that their enemies had pity on them.
Psa106:47 Save us, Lord God! Bring us back from among the nations. Let us celebrate and shout in praise of your holy name.
Psa106:48 Lord God of Israel, you deserve to be praised forever and ever. Let everyone say, "Amen! Shout praises to the Lord !"
Psa107:1 Shout praises to the Lord ! He is good to us, and his love never fails.
Psa107:2 Everyone the Lord has rescued from trouble should praise him,
Psa107:3 everyone he has brought from the east and the west, the north and the south.
Psa107:4 Some of you were lost in the scorching desert, far from a town.
Psa107:5 You were hungry and thirsty and about to give up.
Psa107:6 You were in serious trouble, but you prayed to the Lord , and he rescued you.
Psa107:7 Right away he brought you to a town.
Psa107:8 You should praise the Lord for his love and for the wonderful things he does for all of us.
Psa107:9 To everyone who is thirsty, he gives something to drink; to everyone who is hungry, he gives good things to eat.
Psa107:10 Some of you were prisoners suffering in deepest darkness and bound by chains,
Psa107:11 because you had rebelled against God Most High and refused his advice.
Psa107:12 You were worn out from working like slaves, and no one came to help.
Psa107:13 You were in serious trouble, but you prayed to the Lord , and he rescued you.
Psa107:14 He brought you out of the deepest darkness and broke your chains.
Psa107:15 You should praise the Lord for his love and for the wonderful things he does for all of us.
Psa107:16 He breaks down bronze gates and shatters iron locks.
Psa107:17 Some of you had foolishly committed a lot of sins and were in terrible pain.
Psa107:18 The very thought of food was disgusting to you, and you were almost dead.
Psa107:19 You were in serious trouble, but you prayed to the Lord , and he rescued you.
Psa107:20 By the power of his own word, he healed you and saved you from destruction.
Psa107:21 You should praise the Lord for his love and for the wonderful things he does for all of us.
Psa107:22 You should celebrate by offering sacrifices and singing joyful songs to tell what he has done.
Psa107:23 Some of you made a living by sailing the mighty sea,
Psa107:24 and you saw the miracles the Lord performed there.
Psa107:25 At his command a storm arose, and waves covered the sea.
Psa107:26 You were tossed to the sky and to the ocean depths, until things looked so bad that you lost your courage.
Psa107:27 You staggered like drunkards and gave up all hope.
Psa107:28 You were in serious trouble, but you prayed to the Lord , and he rescued you.
Psa107:29 He made the storm stop and the sea be quiet.
Psa107:30 You were happy because of this, and he brought you to the port where you wanted to go.
Psa107:31 You should praise the Lord for his love and for the wonderful things he does for all of us.
Psa107:32 Honor the Lord when you and your leaders meet to worship.
Psa107:33 If you start doing wrong, the Lord will turn rivers into deserts,
Psa107:34 flowing streams into scorched land, and fruitful fields into beds of salt.
Psa107:35 But the Lord can also turn deserts into lakes and scorched land into flowing streams.
Psa107:36 If you are hungry, you can settle there and build a town.
Psa107:37 You can plant fields and vineyards that produce a good harvest.
Psa107:38 The Lord will bless you with many children and with herds of cattle.
Psa107:39 Sometimes you may be crushed by troubles and sorrows, until only a few of you are left to survive.
Psa107:40 But the Lord will take revenge on those who conquer you, and he will make them wander across desert sands.
Psa107:41 When you are suffering and in need, he will come to your rescue, and your families will grow as fast as a herd of sheep.
Psa107:42 You will see this because you obey the Lord , but everyone who is wicked will be silenced.
Psa107:43 Be wise! Remember this and think about the kindness of the Lord .
Psa108:1 Our God, I am faithful to you with all my heart, and you can trust me. I will sing and play music for you with all that I am.
Psa108:2 I will start playing my harps before the sun rises.
Psa108:3 I will praise you, Lord , for everyone to hear; I will sing hymns to you in every nation.
Psa108:4 Your love reaches higher than the heavens, and your loyalty extends beyond the clouds.
Psa108:5 Our God, may you be honored above the heavens; may your glory be seen everywhere on earth.
Psa108:6 Answer my prayers and use your powerful arm to give us victory. Then the people you love will be safe.
Psa108:7 Our God, from your holy place you made this promise: "I will gladly divide up the city of Shechem and give away Succoth Valley piece by piece.
Psa108:8 The lands of Gilead and Manasseh are mine. Ephraim is my war helmet, and Judah is my symbol of royal power.
Psa108:9 Moab is merely my washbasin, and Edom belongs to me. I shout with victory over the Philistines."
Psa108:10 Our God, who will bring me to the fortress or lead me to Edom?
Psa108:11 Have you rejected us? You don't lead our armies.
Psa108:12 Help us defeat our enemies! No one else can rescue us.
Psa108:13 You are the one who gives us victory and crushes our enemies.
Psa109:1 I praise you, God! Don't keep silent.
Psa109:2 Destructive and deceitful lies are told about me,
Psa109:3 and hateful things are said for no reason.
Psa109:4 I had pity and prayed for my enemies, but their words to me were harsh and cruel.
Psa109:5 For being friendly and kind, they paid me back with meanness and hatred.
Psa109:6 My enemies said, "Find some worthless fools to accuse him of a crime.
Psa109:7 Try him and find him guilty! Consider his prayers a lie.
Psa109:8 Cut his life short and let someone else have his job.
Psa109:9 Make orphans of his children and a widow of his wife;
Psa109:10 make his children beg for food and live in the slums.
Psa109:11 "Let the people he owes take everything he owns. Give it all to strangers.
Psa109:12 Don't let anyone be kind to him or have pity on the children he leaves behind.
Psa109:13 Bring an end to his family, and from now on let him be a forgotten man.
Psa109:14 "Don't let the Lord forgive the sins of his parents and his ancestors.
Psa109:15 Don't let the Lord forget the sins of his family, or let anyone remember his family ever lived.
Psa109:16 He was so cruel to the poor, homeless, and discouraged that they died young.
Psa109:17 "He cursed others. Now place a curse on him! He never wished others well. Wish only trouble for him!
Psa109:18 He cursed others more often than he dressed himself. Let his curses strike him deep, just as water and olive oil soak through to our bones.
Psa109:19 Let his curses surround him, just like the clothes he wears each day."
Psa109:20 Those are the cruel things my enemies wish for me. Let it all happen to them!
Psa109:21 Be true to your name, Lord God! Show your great kindness and rescue me.
Psa109:22 I am poor and helpless, and I have lost all hope.
Psa109:23 I am fading away like an evening shadow; I am tossed aside like a crawling insect.
Psa109:24 I have gone without eating, until my knees are weak, and my body is bony.
Psa109:25 When my enemies see me, they say cruel things and shake their heads.
Psa109:26 Please help me, Lord God! Come and save me because of your love.
Psa109:27 Let others know that you alone have saved me.
Psa109:28 I don't care if they curse me, as long as you bless me. You will make my enemies fail when they attack, and you will make me glad to be your servant.
Psa109:29 You will cover them with shame, just as their bodies are covered with clothes.
Psa109:30 I will sing your praises and thank you, Lord , when your people meet.
Psa109:31 You help everyone in need, and you defend them when they are on trial.
Psa110:1 The Lord said to my Lord, "Sit at my right side, until I make your enemies into a footstool for you."
Psa110:2 The Lord will let your power reach out from Zion, and you will rule over your enemies.
Psa110:3 Your glorious power will be seen on the day you begin to rule. You will wear the sacred robes and shine like the morning sun in all of your strength.
Psa110:4 The Lord has made a promise that will never be broken: "You will be a priest forever, just like Melchizedek."
Psa110:5 My Lord is at your right side, and when he gets angry he will crush the other kings.
Psa110:6 He will judge the nations and crack their skulls, leaving piles of dead bodies all over the earth.
Psa110:7 He will drink from any stream that he chooses, while winning victory after victory.
Psa111:1 Shout praises to the Lord ! With all my heart I will thank the Lord when his people meet.
Psa111:2 The Lord has done many wonderful things! Everyone who is pleased with God's marvelous deeds will keep them in mind.
Psa111:3 Everything the Lord does is glorious and majestic, and his power to bring justice will never end.
Psa111:4 The Lord God is famous for his wonderful deeds, and he is kind and merciful.
Psa111:5 He gives food to his worshipers and always keeps his agreement with them.
Psa111:6 He has shown his mighty power to his people and has given them the lands of other nations.
Psa111:7 God is always honest and fair, and his laws can be trusted.
Psa111:8 They are true and right and will stand forever.
Psa111:9 God rescued his people, and he will never break his agreement with them. He is fearsome and holy.
Psa111:10 Respect and obey the Lord ! This is the first step to wisdom and good sense. God will always be respected.
Psa112:1 Shout praises to the Lord ! The Lord blesses everyone who worships him and gladly obeys his teachings.
Psa112:2 Their descendants will have great power in the land, because the Lord blesses all who do right.
Psa112:3 They will get rich and prosper and will always be remembered for their fairness.
Psa112:4 They will be so kind and merciful and good, that they will be a light in the dark for others who do the right thing.
Psa112:5 Life will go well for those who freely lend and are honest in business.
Psa112:6 They won't ever be troubled, and the kind things they do will never be forgotten.
Psa112:7 Bad news won't bother them; they have decided to trust the Lord .
Psa112:8 They are dependable and not afraid, and they will live to see their enemies defeated.
Psa112:9 They will always be remembered and greatly praised, because they were kind and freely gave to the poor.
Psa112:10 When evil people see this, they angrily bite their tongues and disappear. They will never get what they really want.
Psa113:1 Shout praises to the Lord ! Everyone who serves him, come and praise his name.
Psa113:2 Let the name of the Lord be praised now and forever.
Psa113:3 From dawn until sunset the name of the Lord deserves to be praised.
Psa113:4 The Lord is far above all of the nations; he is more glorious than the heavens.
Psa113:5 No one can compare with the Lord our God. His throne is high above,
Psa113:6 and he looks down to see the heavens and the earth.
Psa113:7 God lifts the poor and needy from dust and ashes,
Psa113:8 and he lets them take part in ruling his people.
Psa113:9 When a wife has no children, he blesses her with some, and she is happy. Shout praises to the Lord !
Psa114:1 God brought his people out of Egypt, that land with a strange language.
Psa114:2 He made Judah his holy place and ruled over Israel.
Psa114:3 When the sea looked at God, it ran away, and the Jordan River flowed upstream.
Psa114:4 The mountains and the hills skipped around like goats.
Psa114:5 Ask the sea why it ran away or ask the Jordan why it flowed upstream.
Psa114:6 Ask the mountains and the hills why they skipped like goats!
Psa114:7 Earth, you will tremble, when the Lord God of Jacob comes near,
