Hag1:7 Think about what I have said!
Hag1:8 But first, go to the hills and get wood for my temple, so I can take pride in it and be worshiped there.
Hag1:9 You expected much, but received only a little. And when you brought it home, I made that little disappear. Why have I done this? It's because you hurry off to build your own houses, while my temple is still in ruins.
