Zec2:6 The Lord says to his people, "Run! Escape from the land in the north, where I scattered you to the four winds.
Zec2:7 Leave Babylonia and hurry back to Zion."
Zec2:8 Then the glorious Lord All-Powerful ordered me to say to the nations that had raided and robbed Zion: Zion is as precious to the Lord as are his eyes. Whatever you do to Zion, you do to him.
Zec2:9 And so, he will put you in the power of your slaves, and they will raid and rob you. Then you will know that I am a prophet of the Lord All-Powerful.
Zec2:10 City of Zion, sing and celebrate! The Lord has promised to come and live with you.
Zec2:11 When he does, many nations will turn to him and become his people. At that time you will know that I am a prophet of the Lord All-Powerful.
Zec2:12 Then Judah will be his part of the holy land, and Jerusalem will again be his chosen city.
Zec2:13 Everyone, be silent! The Lord is present and moving about in his holy place.
