Mat26:4 They planned how they could sneak around and have Jesus arrested and put to death.
Mat26:5 But they said, "We must not do it during Passover, because the people will riot."
Mat26:6 Jesus was in the town of Bethany, eating at the home of Simon, who had leprosy.
Mat26:7 A woman came in with a bottle of expensive perfume and poured it on Jesus' head.
Mat26:8 But when his disciples saw this, they became angry and complained, "Why such a waste?
Mat26:9 We could have sold this perfume for a lot of money and given it to the poor."
Mat26:10 Jesus knew what they were thinking, and he said: Why are you bothering this woman? She has done a beautiful thing for me.
