Mat26:34 Jesus replied, "I promise you that before a rooster crows tonight, you will say three times that you don't know me."
Mat26:35 But Peter said, "Even if I have to die with you, I will never say I don't know you." All the others said the same thing.
Mat26:36 Jesus went with his disciples to a place called Gethsemane. When they got there, he told them, "Sit here while I go over there and pray."
Mat26:37 Jesus took along Peter and the two brothers, James and John. He was very sad and troubled,
Mat26:38 and he said to them, "I am so sad that I feel as if I am dying. Stay here and keep awake with me."
