Mat26:72 Again Peter denied it, and this time he swore, "I don't even know that man!"
Mat26:73 A little while later some people standing there walked over to Peter and said, "We know that you are one of them. We can tell it because you talk like someone from Galilee."
Mat26:74 Peter began to curse and swear, "I don't know that man!" Right then a rooster crowed,
Mat26:75 and Peter remembered that Jesus had said, "Before a rooster crows, you will say three times that you don't know me." Then Peter went out and cried hard.
Mat27:1 Early the next morning all the chief priests and the nation's leaders met and decided that Jesus should be put to death.
Mat27:2 They tied him up and led him away to Pilate the governor.
Mat27:3 Judas had betrayed Jesus, but when he learned that Jesus had been sentenced to death, he was sorry for what he had done. He returned the thirty silver coins to the chief priests and leaders
