Mark8:33 But when Jesus turned and saw the disciples, he corrected Peter. He said to him, "Satan, get away from me! You are thinking like everyone else and not like God."
Mark8:34 Jesus then told the crowd and the disciples to come closer, and he said: If any of you want to be my followers, you must forget about yourself. You must take up your cross and follow me.
Mark8:35 If you want to save your life, you will destroy it. But if you give up your life for me and for the good news, you will save it.
Mark8:36 What will you gain, if you own the whole world but destroy yourself?
Mark8:37 What could you give to get back your soul?
Mark8:38 Don't be ashamed of me and my message among these unfaithful and sinful people! If you are, the Son of Man will be ashamed of you when he comes in the glory of his Father with the holy angels.
Mark9:1 I can assure you that some of the people standing here will not die before they see God's kingdom come with power.
Mark9:2 Six days later Jesus took Peter, James, and John with him. They went up on a high mountain, where they could be alone. There in front of the disciples, Jesus was completely changed.
Mark9:3 And his clothes became much whiter than any bleach on earth could make them.
Mark9:4 Then Moses and Elijah were there talking with Jesus.
Mark9:5 Peter said to Jesus, "Teacher, it is good for us to be here! Let us make three shelters, one for you, one for Moses, and one for Elijah."
Mark9:6 But Peter and the others were terribly frightened, and he did not know what he was talking about.
Mark9:7 The shadow of a cloud passed over and covered them. From the cloud a voice said, "This is my Son, and I love him. Listen to what he says!"
Mark9:8 At once the disciples looked around, but they saw only Jesus.
Mark9:9 As Jesus and his disciples were coming down the mountain, he told them not to say a word about what they had seen, until the Son of Man had been raised from death.
Mark9:10 So they kept it to themselves. But they wondered what he meant by the words "raised from death."
Mark9:11 The disciples asked Jesus, "Don't the teachers of the Law of Moses say that Elijah must come before the Messiah does?"
Mark9:12 Jesus answered: Elijah certainly will come to get everything ready. But don't the Scriptures also say that the Son of Man must suffer terribly and be rejected?
Mark9:13 I can assure you that Elijah has already come. And people treated him just as they wanted to, as the Scriptures say they would.
Mark9:14 When Jesus and his three disciples came back down, they saw a large crowd around the other disciples. The teachers of the Law of Moses were arguing with them.
Mark9:15 The crowd was really surprised to see Jesus, and everyone hurried over to greet him.
Mark9:16 Jesus asked, "What are you arguing about?"
Mark9:17 Someone from the crowd answered, "Teacher, I brought my son to you. A demon keeps him from talking.
Mark9:18 Whenever the demon attacks my son, it throws him to the ground and makes him foam at the mouth and grit his teeth in pain. Then he becomes stiff. I asked your disciples to force out the demon, but they couldn't do it."
Mark9:19 Jesus said, "You people don't have any faith! How much longer must I be with you? Why do I have to put up with you? Bring the boy to me."
Mark9:20 They brought the boy, and as soon as the demon saw Jesus, it made the boy shake all over. He fell down and began rolling on the ground and foaming at the mouth.
Mark9:21 Jesus asked the boy's father, "How long has he been like this?" The man answered, "Ever since he was a child.
Mark9:22 The demon has often tried to kill him by throwing him into a fire or into water. Please have pity and help us if you can!"
Mark9:23 Jesus replied, "Why do you say if you can'? Anything is possible for someone who has faith!"
