John19:20 The words were written in Hebrew, Latin, and Greek. The place where Jesus was taken wasn't far from the city, and many of the Jewish people read the charge against him.
John19:21 So the chief priests went to Pilate and said, "Why did you write that he is King of the Jews? You should have written, He claimed to be King of the Jews.'"
John19:22 But Pilate told them, "What is written will not be changed!"
